Liberia Lawyer Quits Residency Case on Threats, Heritage Reports

-- B y   T e r r e n c e   S e s a y
-- 
2011-09-22T12:12:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/liberia-lawyer-quits-residency-case-on-threats-heritage-reports.html
A lawyer representing a Liberian
political party in a Supreme Court case to decide on residency
requirements for presidential candidates resigned after
receiving death threats,  the Heritage  reported, citing court
proceedings.  Sayma Syrenius Cephus, who represented the Movement for
Progressive Change party, told the court he was unwilling to
risk his life to continue the case, the Monrovia-based newspaper
reported. He did not say who made the threats, according to the
paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Terrence Sesay in Monrovia via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Emily Bowers  at   ebowers1@bloomberg.net . 